Sentencas: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta(BSCF) samples with mixed ionic and electrical conductions as the cathode for solid oxide fuel cell were synthesized via a sol-gel thermolysis method with various pre-sintering temperatures of 450 degrees C, 550 degrees C and 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of pre-sintering temperature and ball-milling on the conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells prepared by sol-gel thermolysis method

Sentencas: The sample which was pre-sintered at 650 degrees C then was ball-milled for 24 h as well.
Titulo: Effect of pre-sintering temperature and ball-milling on the conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells prepared by sol-gel thermolysis method

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscopy (SEM), Brunauer-Emmett-Teller (BET) analysis and DC conductivity of the samples were measured and analyzed.
Titulo: Effect of pre-sintering temperature and ball-milling on the conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells prepared by sol-gel thermolysis method

Sentencas: The result of these analyses demonstrated that all samples had a single phase cubic structure and by increasing the pre-sintering temperature the particle size increased from 0.97 to 1.21 mu m. On the other hand, for the ball-milled sample the particle size decreased to 15 nm.
Titulo: Effect of pre-sintering temperature and ball-milling on the conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells prepared by sol-gel thermolysis method

Sentencas: It was observed that by decreasing the particle size, the electrical conductivity of samples was increased and for the ball-milled sample was reached to 43.29 Scm(-1) at 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of pre-sintering temperature and ball-milling on the conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells prepared by sol-gel thermolysis method

Sentencas: The electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) was used to determine the area specific resistance (ASR), interfacial polarization resistance and its activation energy for fabricated symmetric cells with Samaria-doped ceria (SDC) as an electrolyte and BSCF as electrodes in the temperature range of 500 degrees C to 850 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of pre-sintering temperature and ball-milling on the conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells prepared by sol-gel thermolysis method

Sentencas: The lowest ASR was 0.018 Omega cm(2) at 850 degrees C related to the cell with BSCF pre-sintered at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of pre-sintering temperature and ball-milling on the conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells prepared by sol-gel thermolysis method

Sentencas: For such a cell, the activation energy of interfacial polarization resistance was 127 kJmol(-1).
Titulo: Effect of pre-sintering temperature and ball-milling on the conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells prepared by sol-gel thermolysis method

Sentencas: This property was a result of microstructure, morphology and particle size of BSCF powders.
Titulo: Effect of pre-sintering temperature and ball-milling on the conductivity of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells prepared by sol-gel thermolysis method
